article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 63, Furman 58
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Andrew Goudelock scored 31 points to lead the College of Charleston to a 63-58 win over Furman on Sunday night in the Southern Conference tournament semifinals. Antwaine Wiggins added 10 points, and Trent Wiedeman had 10 points and 12 rebounds for the Cougars (24-9), who will face defending champion Wofford in the championship on Monday. Jordan Miller led the Paladins (22-10) with 11 points and Amu Saaka had 10. Furman held the Cougars without a field goal for almost eight minutes in one stretch in the first half and limited Goudelock to 4-of-13 shooting to take a 29-25 lead at halftime. Furman built an 11-point edge in the second half, but Charleston responded with an 18-3 run to take a 55-51 lead as Furman went more than seven minutes with only three free throws. The Paladins pulled within 59-56 but no closer in the final minute.
